Peter Murungi Has Been Named By The Board Of Directors As The New Managing Director Of Vivo Energy Kenya, The Company That Distributes And Markets Shell Branded Fuels And Lubricants In The Country, Murungi Takes Up His New Role On 1 December 2019. Peter Brings A Wealth Of Experience To The Role, Having Worked For Vivo Energy And Shell Since 2007, Most Recently Leading The Vivo Energy Group’s Implementation Of A New Enterprise Resource Planning System. Peter Holds An MBA As Well As A Bachelor Of Science Degree In Mechanical Engineering From The University Of Nairobi. Peter’s Appointment Follows The Leadership Of Vivo Energy Kenya By Joe Muganda, Who Has Decided To Leave The Company At The End Of November.